This paper deals with the problem of reinforcement learning in non-stationary environments, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on model-based reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly used in robotics and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
